<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="195" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="195">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="195">
(based on 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3486.1.3" author="Coleman, CO" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="195" pagination="63 - 88" refId="B8" refString="Coleman, CO, Lowry, JK, 2012. The genus Pereionotus (Crustacea, Amphipoda, Phliantidae) from Australia. Zootaxa 3486: 63 - 88, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3486.1.3" title="The genus Pereionotus (Crustacea, Amphipoda, Phliantidae) from Australia." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3486.1.3" volume="3486" year="2012">Coleman and Lowry 2012</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="195">Pereon</emphasis>
depressed, coxal plates 1-4 somewhat splayed. Urosome flexed under pleon. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="195">Head</emphasis>
flat with short rostrum. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="195">Maxilla 1</emphasis>
with scale-like inconspicuous palp. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="195">Maxilla 2</emphasis>
with basally fused plates. 
<taxonomicName genus="Maxillipedal" lsidName="Maxillipedal" pageId="0" pageNumber="195" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="195">Maxillipedal</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
palp 3-articulate. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="195">Pereopods</emphasis>
simple. Basis of pereopods 5 and 6 wide, rounded, and ventrally expanded; basis of pereopod 7 without ventral lobe and narrower. Inner ramus of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="195">pleopod 3</emphasis>
slightly shortened. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="195">Uropod 2</emphasis>
uniramous in female, biramous in male. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="195">Uropod 3</emphasis>
without rami.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
